propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.defaultCollapseIcon: The default icon used to collapse the node.
propDescriptions.defaultEndIcon: The default icon displayed next to a end node. This is applied to all tree nodes and can be overridden by the TreeItem icon prop.
propDescriptions.defaultExpandIcon: The default icon used to expand the node.
propDescriptions.defaultParentIcon: The default icon displayed next to a parent node. This is applied to all parent nodes and can be overridden by the TreeItem icon prop.
propDescriptions.defaultSelected: Selected node ids. (Uncontrolled) When multiSelect is true this takes an array of strings; when false (default) a string.
propDescriptions.disabledItemsFocusable: If true, will allow focus on disabled items.
propDescriptions.id: This prop is used to help implement the accessibility logic. If you don't provide this prop. It falls back to a randomly generated id.
propDescriptions.multiSelect: If true ctrl and shift will trigger multiselect.
propDescriptions.onNodeFocus:
Callback fired when tree items are focused.

Signature:
function(event: object, value: string) => void
event: The event source of the callback Warning: This is a generic event not a focus event.
value: of the focused node.
propDescriptions.onNodeSelect:
Callback fired when tree items are selected/unselected.

Signature:
function(event: object, value: array | string) => void
event: The event source of the callback
value: of the selected nodes. When multiSelect is true this is an array of strings; when false (default) a string.
propDescriptions.onNodeToggle:
Callback fired when tree items are expanded/collapsed.

Signature:
function(event: object, nodeIds: array) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
nodeIds: The ids of the expanded nodes.
propDescriptions.selected: Selected node ids. (Controlled) When multiSelect is true this takes an array of strings; when false (default) a string.
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
